<title>
HO2S On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A1306014001">
<title>
HO2S Heater
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect HO2S connector with ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using ohmmeter, measure resistance of HO2S connector (sensor side) of sensor heater between terminals “3” and “4” at sensor connector.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace oxygen sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1306015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Temperature of sensor affects resistance value largely. Make sure that sensor heater is at correct temperature.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
HO2S heater resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
6.0 to 12.0 &#937; at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
</spec>
